FuncDef:
The vsm alarm cpu-performance disable command disables CPU performance log and trap functions on a VSUF-80/VSUF-160/VSUI-160-E/VSUI-400/VSUI-400-E/VSUI-400A/VSUI-400A-E/VSUI-400-S/VSUI-400A-S.
The undo vsm alarm cpu-performance disable command restores the default configuration.
By default, CPU performance log and trap monitoring is enabled on a VSUF-80/VSUF-160/VSUI-160-E/VSUI-400/VSUI-400-E/VSUI-400A/VSUI-400A-E/VSUI-400-S/VSUI-400A-S.
CLIs: vsm alarm cpu-performance { log | trap } disable
undo vsm alarm cpu-performance { log | trap } disable

ParaDef.Info:
Enables or disables CPU performance log monitoring.
-

Enables or disables CPU performance trap monitoring.
-

ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
To disable CPU performance log or trap function on a VSUF-80/VSUF-160/VSUI-160-E/VSUI-400/VSUI-400-E/VSUI-400A/VSUI-400A-E/VSUI-400-S/VSUI-400A-S, run the vsm alarm cpu-performance disable command.
Before configuring an alarm threshold for CPU performance on a VSUF-80/VSUF-160/VSUI-160-E/VSUI-400/VSUI-400-E/VSUI-400A/VSUI-400A-E/VSUI-400-S/VSUI-400A-S, you must run the undo vsm alarm cpu-performance disable command to enable CPU performance log and trap functions on the VSUF-80/VSUF-160/VSUI-160-E/VSUI-400/VSUI-400-E/VSUI-400A/VSUI-400A-E/VSUI-400-S/VSUI-400A-S.
Precautions
In VS mode, this command is supported only by the admin VS.
